        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 1:59AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 159 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
about 13 miles south of Barnhart, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Us-190 Near The Crockett-Sutton County Line, The Intersection Of Us
190 And Highway 163, and Barnhart.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT for west central
Texas.</instruction>
